texts.remarks: Batch edit for Provenance publication project

texts.textentryhtml: Weston’s use of bright, focused light and a dark, saturated background emphasizes the contemplation of the body as a form. He employed similar photographic techniques across disparate subject matter—from the female nude to the depiction of a cabbage leaf seen nearby—focusing not on the content of the image but rather on the composition of contours and shadows captured by the camera’s lens.
